    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe ability for nvim_set_hl to accept the font key was merged in #37668, currently only in nightly. The feature has several issues.\n\n1. If `font` is the *only* key in the `nvim_set_hl` call, the call is dropped.\n2. `hl_combine_attr` forgot to merge `font` values.\n3. `nvim_set_hl` with `update = true` discards the previous font value.\n4. `nvim_set_hl` never stores the font name persistently, so `highlight_attr_set_all`/`set_hl_attr` lose it\n5. `hl_get_attr_by_id` aliases the interned font name into its dict, which `highlight_use_hlstate` later frees, resulting in **use after free** in `nvim__inspect_cell`.\n\nI have fixes for all of these at https://github.com/CGamesPlay/neovim/commit/57d0ccf6333a9e85839918faed7dfa27ed4e250f, PR available upon request.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n  -- font-only highlight is silently dropped\n  vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'FontOnly', { font = 'Monaspace Xenon' })\n  print('font only        :', vim.inspect(vim.api.nvim_get_hl(0, { name = 'FontOnly' })))\n\n  -- same font, plus any real attribute -> survives\n  vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, 'FontPlusFg', { font = 'Monaspace Xenon', fg = '#ff00ff' })\n  print('font + fg        :', vim.inspect(vim.api.nvim_get_hl(0, { name = 'FontPlusFg' })))\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n```\n  font only        : { font = \"Monaspace Xenon\" }\n  font + fg        : { fg = 16711935, font = \"Monaspace Xenon\" }\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nnightly, 9816e939\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, has issues with `nvim_set_hl`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.5.1 (25F80)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNeovide\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nsu (no idea where this comes from)\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
